Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.51,0:00:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fossil evidence clearly shows us that life on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.20,0:00:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't always looked the way it does today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.28,0:00:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Take horses for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.28,0:00:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancestors of our modern horses looked completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.04,0:00:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know that because we have a fantastic fossil record
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.44,0:00:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,stretching back around 60 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.96,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The ancestors of horses were small creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with several toes and they lived in rainforests.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Their small size would have meant that they could hide in the undergrowth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.49,0:00:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and their splayed toes meant that they could walk on marshy ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.39,0:00:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the environment changed. The forest started to disappear and grassland spread out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.60,0:00:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and horses adapted to this changing environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.66,0:00:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They became larger, taller, longer-legged and fleet of foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They were able to range widely across the grasslands eating enough grass
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.14,0:01:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but also being able to run away fast from predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.32,0:01:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And just think about horses' legs today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.70,0:01:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have this many toes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they've reduced down to a single toe on each leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A single toe, and a single hoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.67,0:01:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,
